USE TAB BUTTON FOR AUTOCOMPLETION

rm -rf directoryName                   -> removes the directory and all files and subfolders
rm -r directoryName                    -> removes the directory and all files and subfolders but asks if the user wants to delete each file
mkdir directoryName                    -> creates new directory
ls -A                                  -> lists all files and folders in the current directory
someApp --version                      -> shows the version of the specified software (ex. java --version)
touch fileName                         -> creates new file
chmod +x fileName                      -> makes the file executable
ifconfig                               -> shows network configuration

